condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Appointment of External Auditor | Description: The Recipient shall, not later than four months after theEffective Date, appoint in accordance with the provisions of Section III of this Schedule 2, and thereafter maintain at all timesduring Project implementation, an external auditor for the Project. | Due Date: 17-Aug-2014

Finance Agreement :Auditing of Financial Statements | Description: The Recipient shall have its Financial Statements audited inaccordance with the provisions of Section 4.09 (b) of the General Conditions. Each audit of the Financial Statements shall coverthe period of one Fiscal Year of the Recipient. The audited Financial Statements for each such period shall be furnished to theAssociation not later than six months after the end of such period. | Frequency: Yearly

Finance Agreement :Interim Unaudited Financial Reports | Description:The Recipient shall prepare and furnish to the Association notlater than forty-five days after the end of each calendar quarter, interim unaudited financial reports for the Project covering thequarter, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association. | Frequency: Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Mid-Term Review | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than thirty months after the Effective Date,undertake in conjunction with all agencies involved in the Project, including the national electricity distribution utility onceestablished, a comprehensive mid-term review of the Project. | Due Date :17-Oct-2016

Finance Agreement :Procurement Filing and Record Keeping System | Description: The Recipient shall, not later than three monthsafter the Effective Date, update its procurement filing and record keeping system, in form and substance acceptable to theAssociation. | Due Date: 17-Jul-2014

Finance Agreement: Project Reports | Description :The Recipient shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the Project and prepareProject Reports. Each Project Report shall cover the period of six calendar months, and shall be furnished to the Association notlater than forty-five days after the end of the period covered by such report. | Frequency: Semi-Annually
